    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim does not support this ability yet.\nIt would be useful for projects that has url imports like go and note taking apps in neovim like zk-nvim and obsidian.nvim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n1. `vim.lsp.buf.document_link` should open a loclist like `vim.lsp.buf.document_symbol`, and 1) jumps to the local file or 2) jump the external url location in the current file\n2. if a client is attached and supports `textDocument/DocumentLink` then in that buffer `gx` is mapped to use lsp provided info.\n\nThere is already a plugin [lsplink.nvim](https://github.com/icholy/lsplinks.nvim), and I have made some progress with adding a provider and working with `gopls` and `zk-lsp`, will work on this and submit a PR.\n\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/16c658da-886b-4ac6-aa00-810e6c21c43e)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fe7fa3a9-15a9-44e9-8c6e-3f9980d57c75)",
